Text:
On their day off, Skel, Po, and Cid go shopping
together, like proper side characters.
You've been waiting for this!
Garter Corporation is your home's ultimate companion!
Our autumn sale is now underway!
Whoa...!
Listen up! We're heading into an all-out bloodbath!
Outta the way!
Our target is the 50% off itemsâ€”
Move!

Step right this way! Don't miss out on our products,
too!
Not just Garter! Today, everything's on sale!

Thank you for supporting our community-based Racket
Corporation!

(A full-blown bargain sale in the shopping
district...)
We won't let Mitsugoshi beat us!

(At the end of the day, Alpha and the others went too
far.)

(They sold exclusively through their directly managed
stores, sidelining local businesses. Thanks to that,
both the big players and small shops in the downtown
districts view them as a threat.)

(With this level of resentment from their industry
peers...)

(I see. Like Yukime said, Mitsugoshi's future looks
pretty bleak.)
Destroy it all, then start from scratch...

(Mitsugoshi will get crushed by the MCA, and I'll
take down the MCA. I'll make a new company in the
brand-new marketplace using the vast remaining
assets.)

(I'll hire Alpha and the others to run that company.
In other words, Mitsugoshi will simply be reborn
under a different name.)
(Once all this is over, the girls will realize...)
(...this was for the best...)
That'll be 5,000 zeni!

When it comes to taking back damaged products, that's
where Mitsugoshi outdoes the other stores...
Isn't that a given?
Your change is 1,750 zeni.

(More to the point, it seems like people have started
using paper currency recently. The Midgar Kingdom
fundamentally runs on a coin-based economy, but
bills have made some serious inroads.)
Huh...?
What's up with that bill?
Whaddaya mean?
Did they always look like that?
Oh, this is one of the new bills the MCA just put out.

Today's the big sale commemorating the MCA releasing
their new bills, right?
What were the bills we used to use?
These.
Mitsugoshi banknotes.
Mitsugoshi...

They used to only be accepted at Mitsugoshi's own
stores.
Now, they're usable all over the capital.

I was thinking about using them with the peddlers
over summer breakâ€”

(So, they've even extended their influence to
banks...)

(I vaguely remember discussing "banks" and "credit
creation" from a MBO documentary I once watched...)
But even if there's volatility in the market...
You could use a provider with a different rate...

But liquidity isn't stable, it's dynamic, both rising
and falling...

(I'm pretty sure I wrapped up the conversation when
my hazy knowledge started to sound questionable...)

(But now we're talking about counterfeits...I mean,
respectful imitations being in circulation.)
What do we do now?
Wanna go to karaoke?
(Counterfeits?)

(Mitsugoshi's bills have multi-color printing and
even a watermark...)

(But this counterfeit looks crude, with a basic
design...)
(Hold on...)
I once had this dream when I was a kid.
Hm?

I thought I could duplicate the remaining 1,000 yen
from my New Year's money...using the copy machine
at a convenience storeâ€¦
What're you talking about?
...By the way, please give me back my money.

Back then, the elderly shop staff gave me a real
earful, so I had to drop the idea...
What're you even talking about?
Cid, my money.
Right now, I'm...a super elite agent.
I'll make my dream come true!
Cid!
Cid!!!
C'mon, brain! Focus! Remember!
I'm counting on you, MBO!
Ciiiiid!!!
Cid, my moneyyy!
